@NODE NO50 "Note"
Il  titolo  originale fa riferimento a un passo di Romeo and Juliet di
William Shakespeare in cui Juliet é al balcone e dice:

@{i}What's  in  a name?  That which we call a rose by any other name would
smell as sweet, so too would Romeo, if separated from his name, retain
that  sweet  perfection  which is his own.@{ui} (Romeo and Juliet, II, ii, 43)
@ENDNODE
