@NODE 0394 "Citazioni"

@{b}Sisko:@{ub}  We need a Community Leader, and it's going to be you, Quark!
@{b}Quark:@{ub} Ahahahah Community Leader! Ahahahah
@{b}Odo:@{ub}   Seems  reasonable:   you  have all the character reference of a
politician.

@{b}O'Brien:@{ub}   Computer,  transfer  energy  from  the  inertial dampers to
reinforce the subspace field.
@{b}Computer:@{ub} Procedure is not recommended.
@{b}O'Brien:@{ub} Damn it transfer the energy!
@{b}Computer:@{ub}   Unable to comply.  Level 1 safety protocols have cancelled
the request.
@{b}O'Brien:@{ub} Cancelled?
@{b}Computer:@{ub}   Warning:   subspace  field  collapse  in  30  seconds.
[...]
@{b}O'Brien:@{ub}  Computer, you and I need to have a little talk

@{b}Sisko:@{ub}   In  a  linear  existance, we can't go back to the past to get
something we've left behind, so it's lost.
@{b}Alien:@{ub}   It's  inconceivable  that  any  species could exist in such a
manner:  you are deceiving us.

@{b}Alien:@{ub} You value your ignorance of what is to come?
@{b}Sisko:@{ub}   That  may  be  the  most  important thing to understand about
humans.  It is the unknown that defines our existance.
@ENDNODE


@{b}Kira:@{ub} Shields Up!
@{b}O'Brien:@{ub} What shields?

@{b}Kira:@{ub}  If you don't take that hand off my hip, you'll never be able to
raise a glass with it again.
@{b}Quark:@{ub}  Ohhh I love women in an uniform.


@NODE 0395 "Citazioni"

@{b}Odo:@{ub}   And we have specific regulations:  you can leave your weapon or
leave the station.  Your choice:  please make it now.
@{b}Klingon:@{ub}  Who are you?
@{b}Odo:@{ub}  I'm the one giving you the choice.
@ENDNODE
@NODE 0396 "Citazioni"

@{b}Odo:@{ub} I'll never understand the humanoid need to... couple
@{b}Quark:@{ub} You've never... coupled???
@{b}Odo:@{ub} Choosed not to. Too many compromises...

@{b}Quark  (a  proposito di Dax e Sisko):@{ub}  I Know for a fact that when she
was  a  he...   you  know, before she got this new body, they were old
friends...
@{b}Odo:@{ub} Things change.
@ENDNODE
@NODE 0397 "Citazioni"

@{b}O'Brien:@{ub}    Should  I  transfer  to  a  cargo-drone?   No  people,  no
complaints.

@{b}Kira:@{ub}   Listen  Surmak, I have a station full of dying people, and you
are the closest thing to an expert on this virus.
@{b}Surmak:@{ub} I simpathize Major, but I don't think I can help you.
@{b}Kira:@{ub} All right. Then how about helping yourself?
@{b}Surmak:@{ub} Meaning what?
@{b}Kira:@{ub}   Meaning  I've  been  infected  with your virus, doctor, so now
you're infected too.

@{b}Quark:@{ub} Odo? Quark to Odo You still there?
@{b}Odo:@{ub} Try not to sound too disappointed
@ENDNODE
@NODE 0398 "Citazioni"

@{b}Tosk:@{ub} I am Tosk
@{b}O'Brien:@{ub} That's your name, or your species?
@{b}Tosk:@{ub} I am Tosk

@{b}O'Brien:@{ub} How about you are you an explorer, or scientist?
@{b}Tosk:@{ub} I am Tosk.

@{b}O'Brien  a Tosk su Quark:@{ub}  and the man who'll exploit any vice you may
have.
@{b}Tosk a Quark:@{ub} I'm sorry, I have no vice to exploit.
@{b}Quark:@{ub} A challenge...

@{b}Tosk:@{ub} I'm Tosk
@{b}Odo:@{ub} I'm sure you are...
@ENDNODE
@NODE 0399 "Citazioni"

@{b}Dax  (a Mora Pol, a proposito di Odo):@{ub}  "When did you realize you were
dealing with a sentient life form?
@{b}Odo:@{ub} He didn't. I had to teach him by myself ...

@{b}Bashir (a Dax):@{ub} My replicator or yours?

@{b}Mora Pol:@{ub} Constable.
@{b}Odo:@{ub} It's a nickname that I barely tolerate.
@{b}Mora  Pol:@{ub}  It's an expression of affection that you find difficult to
accept.
@ENDNODE
@NODE 039a "Citazioni"

@{b}Q:@{ub} You hit me! Picard never hit me.
@{b}Sisko:@{ub} I am NOT Picard!
@ENDNODE
@NODE 039b "Citazioni"

@{b}Odo:@{ub}  because women don't react to me in that manner!
@{b}Dax:@{ub} Are you saying that you've never had a female friend?
@{b}Odo:@{ub} I consider Major Kira a friend.
@{b}Dax:@{ub}   That's  not  what  I  meant.   I'm  talking  about  an intimate
friendship.
@{b}Odo:@{ub} That's a very personal question.
@{b}Dax:@{ub}  I'm sorry, but after seven lifetimes impersonal questions aren't
much fun anymore.

@{b}Quark:@{ub} You make it sound like you don'like me.
@{b}Kira:@{ub}   Don't  like  you?   You collaborated with the Cardassians, you
cheat  your  customers,  and you are a danger to the station.  I don't
just 'not like' you, I despise you!
@{b}Quark:@{ub} Sorry I mentioned it.

@{b}Vedek  Bareil:@{ub}  to be honest, I had been looking for an opportunity to
see you.
@{b}Kira:@{ub} Really? I'm honored.
@{b}Vedek Bareil:@{ub} Ehm actually I was hoping you'd be happy to see me.
@{b}Kira:@{ub} Oh, I'm very happy.
@ENDNODE
@NODE 039c "Citazioni"

@{b}Quark [a Dax]:@{ub} You can't quit now! You've just won!

@{b}Dax  [a Arjin]:@{ub}  So, you don't play tango, you don't wrestle, what are
we going to do while you're here?

@{b}Dax:@{ub}   Arjin, if you truly want to became a Trill host some day you'll
never call me madam again.
@{b}Arjin:@{ub} Yes, Lieutenant.
@{b}Dax:@{ub} Why don't you try 'Jadzia'?
@{b}Arjin:@{ub} If you think that's appropriate
@{b}Dax:@{ub}  Oh, I'm sure it isn't appropriate at all, but then, I hate to be
appropriate.

@{b}Quark:@{ub}   Rule  of  Aquisition  1-12:   Never  have  sex with the boss'
sister.
@ENDNODE
@NODE 039d "Citazioni"

@{b}Quark [a Odo]:@{ub}  You've got all the emotions of a stone!
@ENDNODE
@NODE 039e "Citazioni"

@{b}Cos:@{ub}   in the end, it all comes down to luck.

@{b}Quark:@{uub}   The 47th rule of acquisition says @{i}"Don't trust a man with a better
suit than your own"@{ui}

@{b}Quark:@{ub}   and  the  challenger:  he's fast, he's deadly, he's Julian Bashir.
They call him "the doctor".

@{b}Martus:@{ub} I still have my dignity!
@{b}Quark:@{ub}  Dignity in an empty sack isn't worth the sack:  rule of acquisition
number nine.
@ENDNODE
